#4501
The White Steps~
White marble steps lead up from the ground level of the street and rise
up in stages towards the doorway of the courthouse.  Lining each side of the
white steps, green banzai trees have been planted in large, decorative
pots, though they have all been trimmed into a different shape.  Colorful
tiles has been placed into the center of the marble steps, allowing one to
view it from standing back and get the image of a large rose growing up the
stairway.  At the top of the staircase, the entrance to the courthouse can
be seen, while west of here leads back to the street.  
