A Grand Entranceway~
This wide veranda has been decorated with a variety of plants and
flowers, though the most abundant appears to be white roses.  The large pots
have been arranged in a way to provide room for people to browse through
them and for benches to be set up in obscure places for conversing.  The
center of the northern wall is interrupted only by a pair of elegant, dark
brown doors.  A flight of steps made of marble leads down towards the
streets, while the doorway to the north provides entrance into the
courthouse.  
